main event: An unidentified bright object was seen making a low arc and striking water north of the Hawaiian Islands on 7th November 1959.
interesting points: The object struck the water approximately four miles north of the witnesses' position before changing course and emitting at least three flashes.
The sighting lasted for twenty to thirty seconds and was witnessed by three reputable individuals.
The document includes communication between different Air Force bases and divisions to determine if the object could have been a known missile or satellite, but the results were negative.
The conclusion drawn was that it was highly probable that the witnesses saw a meteor which appeared to strike the water but, in reality, passed below the horizon.
The report indicates that there were no additional details available at the headquarters about the incident.
